data.name: richTxtDirections.Text
data.value:
AutoMouse is a simple program to prevent the screensaver from disrupting presentations or video playback.
Since this program bypasses domain security policy, please be conscientious to only enable this program when absolutely needed to prevent the disruption of the display (ie., for presentations or video playback). The domain security policy helps to prevent unauthorized access to corporate networks, computers, and devices.
Main Program Dialog ----------------------------------------------------- Frequency (seconds): A whole number between 2 and 1800 that represents the time between each AutoMouse movement. Enabled: If this box is checked, AutoMouse is running and will move the mouse automatically based on the frequency setting. If it is unchecked, AutoMouse will be disabled. Left click after moving: If this box is checked, the left mouse button will be clicked after performing each AutoMouse movement.
Minimized Program (System Tray) ----------------------------------------------------- Right-click the tray icon to access the AutoMouse context menu. Exit: Stops AutoMouse and kills the program. Restore: Shows the main program dialog window. Enabled: If this menu item is checked, AutoMouse is running and will move the mouse automatically based on the frequency setting (mouse icon with green plus). If it is unchecked, AutoMouse will be disabled (mouse icon with red minus). Double-clicking the tray icon will restore the main program dialog window.
Updating ----------------------------------------------------- If you are connected to the internet, AutoMouse will check for updates when the program is started. If there is an update, AutoMouse will prompt you to install the update the next time the program runs. Alternatively, you can choose "Check for Update" from the "Help" menu to manually check and install any available updates.
